dc_title_s: Map of the North West Territory illustrating the British and United States boundary line. Surveyed and marked out by the Joint Commission, 1872-3-4. To accompany the paper by Captn. Anderson R.E. / [engraved by] Edwd. Weller, F.R.G.S.
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures. International Boundary from Lake of the Woods to approx. 115° west longitude is shown. Route of Boundary Commission and projected route of Canada Pacific R[ail] R[oad] and connection with United States are shown. Major lakes, rivers, mountains, and plains are shown. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 46 (1876), pp. 228-62; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v. 46 1876
